Description: Maximum E-State index (electrotopological state index) for a molecule. Reference for E-State indices: https://doi.org/10.1002/qsar.19910100108
Minimum E-State index (electrotopological state index) for a molecule. Reference for E-State indices: https://doi.org/10.1002/qsar.19910100108
Maximum (disregarding the sign) E-State index (electrotopological state index) for a molecule. Reference for E-State indices: https://doi.org/10.1002/qsar.19910100108
Minimum (disregarding the sign) E-State index (electrotopological state index) for a molecule. Reference for E-State indices: https://doi.org/10.1002/qsar.19910100108
Calculate the weighted sum of ADS mapped properties
The average molecular weight of the molecule
The average molecular weight of the molecule ignoring hydrogens
The exact molecular weight of the molecule
The number of valence electrons the molecule has
The number of radical electrons the molecule has (says nothing about spin state)
Largest Gasteiger partial charge in a molecule. Reference for Gasteiger partial charge: https://doi.org/10.1016/0040-4020(80)80168-2
Smallest Gasteiger partial charge in a molecule. Reference for Gasteiger partial charge: https://doi.org/10.1016/0040-4020(80)80168-2
Largest (disregarding the sign) Gasteiger partial charge in a molecule. Reference for Gasteiger partial charge: https://doi.org/10.1016/0040-4020(80)80168-2
Smallest (disregarding the sign) Gasteiger partial charge in a molecule. Reference for Gasteiger partial charge: https://doi.org/10.1016/0040-4020(80)80168-2
Morgan fingerprint (radius 1) density. The density is taken as the number of "on" bits/non-zero bits divided by the number of heavy atoms.
Morgan fingerprint (radius 2) density. The density is taken as the number of "on" bits/non-zero bits divided by the number of heavy atoms.
Morgan fingerprint (radius 3) density. The density is taken as the number of "on" bits/non-zero bits divided by the number of heavy atoms.
BCUT descriptor (Mass eigenvalue high). Reference: https://doi.org/10.1021/ci980102x
BCUT descriptor (Mass eigenvalue low). Reference: https://doi.org/10.1021/ci980102x
BCUT descriptor (Gasteiger charge eigenvalue high). Reference: https://doi.org/10.1021/ci980102x
BCUT descriptor (Gasteiger charge eigenvalue low). Reference: https://doi.org/10.1021/ci980102x
BCUT descriptor (Crippen logP eigenvalue high). Reference: https://doi.org/10.1021/ci980102x
BCUT descriptor (Crippen logP eigenvalue low). Reference: https://doi.org/10.1021/ci980102x

BCUT descriptor (Crippen MR, eigenvalue low). Reference: https://doi.org/10.1021/ci980102x
Calculate Balaban's J value for a molecule. We follow the notation of Balaban's paper: https://doi.org/10.1016/0009-2614(82)80009-2

A topological index meant to quantify "complexity" of molecules. Consists of a sum of two terms, one representing the complexity of the bonding, the other representing the complexity of the distribution of heteroatoms. From https://doi.org/10.1021/ja00402a071
Similar to Hall Kier Chi0v, but uses nVal instead of valence.

Similar to Hall Kier Chi3v, but uses nVal instead of valence.
Similar to Hall Kier Chi4v, but uses nVal instead of valence.
The Hall-Kier alpha value for a molecule. From equations (58) of https://doi.org/10.1002/9780470125793.ch9
